  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Land Surveyors",
  "description": "<p>The <strong>Land Surveyor</strong> is responsible in ensuring accurate land measurements and site layout for building projects undertaken by the Company.</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Conduct land, topographical, and as-built surveys for construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Perform site setting-out and verification in accordance with engineering drawings.</li>\n  <li>Use surveying instruments (Total Station, GPS, Levels) to gather field data.</li>\n  <li>Prepare survey reports, drawings, and maintain proper documentation.</li>\n  <li>Work closely with project managers, engineers, and site teams to ensure alignment and accuracy.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all work complies with regulatory and safety standards.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>The Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Degree in Land Surveying, Geomatics, or related field with minimum 5 years of relevant experience in construction projects.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in surveying software and equipment (e.g., Leica, Trimble, AutoCAD).</li>\n  <li><strong>Registered Surveyor under SISV</strong> will be an <strong>added advantage</strong>.</li>\n  <li><strong>Willingness to work night shifts</strong> will be an <strong>added advantage</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Strong attention to detail and excellent communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Must have experience with BTO and gov sector </li>\n</ul>",
